==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*χwerƀ-'' ‘turn’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[hwerva]], Old Saxon [[hwerƀan]], Old High German [[hwerban]], Old Norse [[hverfa]].

===Pronounciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hweoɹvan/

===Verb===
'''hweorfan''' (strong verb class III: '''hweorfeþ''' ‘he turns’; '''hwearf''' ‘he turned’; '''hwurfon''' ‘they turned’; '''ġehworden''' past participle)
# to [[turn]]
# to [[depart]]
# to [[travel]], [[roam]]

